item.title: CVE-2019-1794|2024-09-16T16:23:48.538Z -- cisco -- cisco%20directory%20connector
item.description: A vulnerability in the search path processing of Cisco Directory Connector could allow an authenticated, local attacker to load a binary of their choosing. The vulnerability is due to uncontrolled search path elements. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability by placing a binary of their choosing earlier in the search path utilized by Cisco Directory Connector to locate and load required resources.
